<h2>The question</h2>
<p>
  The <strong>before/after annotated visual-diff surface</strong> shows <strong>two renders of one
  subject</strong> — a baseline vs a new capture, or a design vs a built screen — side-by-side, with the
  regions that differ called out as <strong>numbered, clickable, typed regions</strong>, each carrying a
  <strong>per-region review verdict</strong> (accept the change, reject it as a regression, or mark it
  <em>expected but not reached yet</em>). It cleared the corrected minting bar as a <strong>candidate</strong>
  in <a href="/backlog/2533-console-board-derived-ui-standards/">#2533</a> Fork 5; what was missing was the
  <strong>contract shape</strong>, not the justification. This topic shapes the three open questions — the
  <strong>delta-type taxonomy</strong>, the <strong>anchor payload</strong>, and the
  <strong>accept / typed-region model</strong> — measured against the nearest existing standard,
  <a href="/intents/audit-timeline/">Audit Timeline</a>, and recommends <strong>MINT a <code>visual-diff</code>
  intent</strong>. Prepares decision <a href="/backlog/2538-shape-the-annotated-visual-diff-surface-contract-then-decide-mint/">#2538</a>.
</p>

<h2>Why audit-timeline does not cover it</h2>
<p>
  <a href="/intents/audit-timeline/">Audit Timeline</a> is a <strong>chronological text/event feed</strong> of
  <code>AuditEvent</code>s for one entity — it is temporal and linear, and it "owns the display, not the
  record." The visual-diff surface is <strong>spatial and two-pane</strong>, and its unit is a <em>region of
  divergence between two renders</em>, not an event in a stream. audit-timeline cannot express
  <em>"these two rendered states differ <strong>here</strong>, and the difference is <strong>this kind</strong>."</em>
  The gap is real; audit-timeline is the nearest-but-non-covering neighbor.
</p>

<h2>Prior art — the shipped models</h2>
